{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd9b7690-02a0-4671-bd36-66c785a2c050","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   - Upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it includes Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`.\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if you need TRX output (optional).\n\n2. **Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   The `dotnet test` command now routes through Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest.\n\n4. **Optional — generate a program entry point** for more control (e.g., custom extensions):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>false</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   Then add a `Program.cs` manually using `NUnit.Testing.Platform`.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **v5+** dropped VSTest support — it *only* targets Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- If you need to keep VSTest alongside, stay on 4.x and use the `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` bridge package instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79bb4c51-130d-40c6-9d0c-2d1161bde204","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files, I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":435,"requestId":"A02E:39BFD7:B88178:D88DD0:69FE84F6"},"id":"18ac8749-3c69-4fdd-a5ab-5c5ae280aabd","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:13.319Z","parentId":"2e68f989-6b81-435e-86d0-4ba15d64101a"}
